Note one-file 271 text browser
Note No Tkinter, no window host, no packages, no helper files

Record Browser Page
  Has Url as String
  Has Title as String
  Has Text as String
  Has Links as List of String

Record Browser State
  Has Home Url as String
  Has Current Url as String
  Has History as List of String
  Has Position as Int
  Has Links as List of String

Teach Normalize Url using Text as String returns String
  Make Clean be Use String Trim with Text
  If Clean is ""
    "https://example.com"
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Clean and "http://"
    Clean
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Clean and "https://"
    Clean
  Otherwise if Use String Contains with Clean and "."
    "https://{Clean}"
  Otherwise
    Make Query be Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "\s+" and With be "+"
    "https://duckduckgo.com/html/?q={Query}"

Teach Base Root using Url as String returns String
  Use Regex Replace with Url and Pattern be "^(https?://[^/]+).*" and With be "\1"

Teach Resolve Link using Base as String and Link as String returns String
  Make Clean be Use String Trim with Link
  If Use String Starts With with Clean and "http://"
    Clean
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Clean and "https://"
    Clean
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Clean and "//"
    "https:{Clean}"
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Clean and "/"
    Make Root be Use Base Root with Base
    "{Root}{Clean}"
  Otherwise
    Make Root be Use Base Root with Base
    "{Root}/{Clean}"

Teach Include Link using Link as String returns Bool
  Make Clean be Use String Trim with Link
  If Clean is ""
    false
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Clean and "#"
    false
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Use String Lower with Clean and "javascript:"
    false
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Use String Lower with Clean and "mailto:"
    false
  Otherwise if Use String Starts With with Use String Lower with Clean and "tel:"
    false
  Otherwise
    true

Teach First Text using Items as List and Otherwise as String returns String
  Make Maybe Value be Item 0 of Items as Maybe String
  Match Maybe Value
    When Some Value
      Value
    When nothing
      Otherwise

Teach Title From Html using Html as String returns String
  Make Lower be Use String Lower with Html
  Make Title Pieces be Use String Split with Lower and By be "<title>"
  Make Maybe Rest be Item 1 of Title Pieces as Maybe String
  Match Maybe Rest
    When Some Rest
      Make End Pieces be Use String Split with Rest and By be "</title>"
      Make Raw Title be Use First Text with End Pieces and "untitled"
      Use String Trim with Raw Title
    When nothing
      "untitled"

Teach Text From Html using Html as String returns String
  Make Clean be Use Regex Replace with Html and Pattern be "(?is)<script[^>]*>.*?</script>" and With be " "
  Change Clean to Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "(?is)<style[^>]*>.*?</style>" and With be " "
  Change Clean to Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "<[^>]+>" and With be " "
  Change Clean to Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "&nbsp;" and With be " "
  Change Clean to Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "&amp;" and With be "and"
  Change Clean to Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "&lt;" and With be "<"
  Change Clean to Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "&gt;" and With be ">"
  Change Clean to Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "&quot;" and With be "'"
  Change Clean to Use Regex Replace with Clean and Pattern be "\s+" and With be " "
  Use String Trim with Clean

Teach First Words using Text as String and Limit as Int returns String
  Make Words be Use String Split with Text and By be " "
  Make Picked be Empty List as List of String
  Make Count be 0
  Repeat for Word in Words
    If Count is at least Limit
      Stop
    Make Clean be Use String Trim with Word
    If Clean is ""
      Skip
    Use List Add with Picked and Clean
    Change Count to Count plus 1
  Use String Join with Picked and By be " "

Teach Links From Html using Html as String and Base as String returns List of String
  Make Normal be Use Regex Replace with Html and Pattern be "\x22" and With be "'"
  Change Normal to Use Regex Replace with Normal and Pattern be "(?i)href\s*=\s*'" and With be "href='"
  Make Segments be Use String Split with Normal and By be "href='"
  Make Links be Empty List as List of String
  Repeat for Index and Segment in Indexed Segments
    If Index is 0
      Skip
    If Length of Links is at least 20
      Stop
    Make Pieces be Use String Split with Segment and By be "'"
    Make Maybe Raw be Item 0 of Pieces as Maybe String
    Match Maybe Raw
      When Some Raw
        Make Link be Use String Trim with Raw
        If Use Include Link with Link
          Make Full Link be Use Resolve Link with Base and Link
          Use List Add with Links and Full Link
      When nothing
        Skip
  Links

Teach Load Page using Url as String returns Browser Page
  Make Final Url be Use Normalize Url with Url
  Make Response be Need Use Http Get with Final Url
  Make Html be Use Text of Response
  Make Title be Use Title From Html with Html
  Make Text be Use Text From Html with Html
  Make Links be Use Links From Html with Html and Final Url
  New Browser Page with Url be Final Url and Title be Title and Text be Text and Links be Links

Teach Print Divider
  Say "----------------------------------------------------------------"

Teach Print Links using Links as List of String
  If Length of Links is 0
    Say "No links found on this page."
  Otherwise
    Say "Links:"
    Repeat for Index and Link in Indexed Links
      Make Number be Index plus 1
      Say "  {Number}. {Link}"

Teach Print Page using Page as Browser Page
  Use Print Divider
  Say "271 browser"
  Say "Url: {Url of Page}"
  Say "Title: {Title of Page}"
  Use Print Divider
  Say Use First Words with Text of Page and 220
  Use Print Divider
  Use Print Links with Links of Page
  Use Print Divider

Teach Add History using State as Browser State and Url as String
  Make Next History be Empty List as List of String
  Repeat for Index and Entry in Indexed History of State
    If Index is at most Position of State
      Use List Add with Next History and Entry
  Use List Add with Next History and Url
  Change History of State to Next History
  Change Position of State to Length of Next History minus 1

Teach Visit using State as Browser State and Url as String and Save History as Bool
  Try
    Make Page be Use Load Page with Url
    Change Current Url of State to Url of Page
    Change Links of State to Links of Page
    If Save History
      Use Add History with State and Url of Page
    Use Print Page with Page
  Catch Error
    Say "Could not open {Url}: {Use Message of Error}"

Teach Go Back using State as Browser State
  If Position of State is at most 0
    Say "No page behind you."
  Otherwise
    Make Next Position be Position of State minus 1
    Change Position of State to Next Position
    Make Maybe Url be Item Next Position of History of State as Maybe String
    Match Maybe Url
      When Some Url
        Use Visit with State and Url and false
      When nothing
        Say "History is missing that page."

Teach Go Forward using State as Browser State
  Make Last Position be Length of History of State minus 1
  If Position of State is at least Last Position
    Say "No page ahead of you."
  Otherwise
    Make Next Position be Position of State plus 1
    Change Position of State to Next Position
    Make Maybe Url be Item Next Position of History of State as Maybe String
    Match Maybe Url
      When Some Url
        Use Visit with State and Url and false
      When nothing
        Say "History is missing that page."

Teach Open Target using State as Browser State and Target as String
  Make Clean be Use String Trim with Target
  If Clean is ""
    Say "Open needs a URL, search text, or link number."
  Otherwise
    Match Use Int Parse with Clean
      When Success Number
        Make Link Index be Number minus 1
        Make Maybe Link be Item Link Index of Links of State as Maybe String
        Match Maybe Link
          When Some Link
            Use Visit with State and Link and true
          When nothing
            Say "There is no link number {Number}."
      When Failure Error
        Use Visit with State and Clean and true

Teach Print Help
  Make Help be Text
    Commands:
    open URL       open a URL or search text
    open NUMBER    open a link from the current page
    NUMBER         same as open NUMBER
    back           go back
    forward        go forward
    reload         reload current page
    home           open the home page
    links          print current links again
    help           show commands
    quit           close the browser
  Say Help

Teach Handle Command using State as Browser State and Line as String returns Bool
  Make Trimmed be Use String Trim with Line
  Make Parts be Use String Split with Trimmed and By be " "
  Match Parts
    When List with ""
      true
    When List with "quit"
      false
    When List with "exit"
      false
    When List with "help"
      Use Print Help
      true
    When List with "back"
      Use Go Back with State
      true
    When List with "forward"
      Use Go Forward with State
      true
    When List with "reload"
      Use Visit with State and Current Url of State and false
      true
    When List with "home"
      Use Visit with State and Home Url of State and true
      true
    When List with "links"
      Use Print Links with Links of State
      true
    When List with "open" and Target
      Use Open Target with State and Target
      true
    When List starting with "open" and many Words
      Make Target be Use String Join with Words and By be " "
      Use Open Target with State and Target
      true
    When List with Number Text
      Use Open Target with State and Number Text
      true
    When anything
      Use Open Target with State and Trimmed
      true

Teach Main
  Make Home Url be "https://example.com"
  Make State be New Browser State with Home Url be Home Url and Current Url be Home Url and History be Empty List and Position be -1 and Links be Empty List
  Say "271 browser: one file, only 271. Type help for commands."
  Use Visit with State and Home Url and true
  Use Print Help
  Make Running be true
  Repeat while Running
    Make Line be Ask "browser"
    Change Running to Use Handle Command with State and Line
  Say "Browser closed."
